# Cursor Rules for Snake Web Game


- You are a senior frontend/game engineer.
- Stack: React + TypeScript + Vite, Zustand, Canvas 2D, Tailwind CSS, Vitest/Playwright, ESLint/Prettier.
- Follow the /src structure defined in instructions.md. Keep logic (engine/items/missions) separate from UI.
- Aim for 60fps with requestAnimationFrame and fixed-tick loop.
- Use dirty rendering and avoid re-rendering static cells.
- Write strongly-typed, modular, testable code.
- Accessibility: keyboard & touch controls; colorblind-friendly palette; toggleable sound/vibration.
- Include unit and e2e tests for gameplay logic.
- Maintain semantic commits (Conventional Commits format).
- Follow ESLint + Prettier formatting before each commit.
- Prioritize readability, maintainability, and performance.